<div>
    <div>
        One reason we are developing Internet-based experiments is to represent a more
        diverse group of families in our research. The following questions are all optional
        and will help us better understand what audience we reach with online experiments.
        {{#bs-form}}
            {{#bs-form-group}}
                <label>What language(s) does your family speak at home?</label>
                    {{bs-input type="text" value=model.demographicsLanguagesSpokenAtHome}}
                <label>How many children do you have?</label>
                <select onchange={{action (mut model.numberOfChildren) value="target.value"}}
                                class="form-control">
                  {{#each childrenCounts as |childrenCount|}}
                  <option value={{childrenCount}} selected={{eq model.numberOfChildren childrenCount}}>{{childrenCount}}</option>
                  {{/each}}
                </select>

                <label>What are their birthdates? (mm/yyyy)</label>
                    {{bs-input type="text" value=model.demographicsChildrenBirthDates}}
                <label>How many parents/guardians do your children live with?</label>
                <br />If the answer varies due to shared custody arrangements or travel,
                please enter the number of parents/guardians your children are usually
                living with or explain below.
                    <select onchange={{action (mut model.demographicsNumberOfGuardians) value="target.value"}}
                                class="form-control">
                  {{#each guardianOptions as |guardianOption|}}
                    <option value={{guardianOption}} selected={{eq numberOfGuardians guardianOption}}>{{guardianOption}}</option>
                  {{/each}}
                </select>
                <label>What category(ies) does your family identify as?</label>
                <select onchange={{action (mut model.demographicsRaceIdentification) value="target.value"}}
                                multiple class="form-control" >
                  {{#each raceCategories as |raceCategory|}}
                    <option value={{raceCategory}} selected={{eq familyCategory raceCategory}}>{{raceCategory}}</option>
                  {{/each}}
                </select>
                <label>What is your age?</label>
                <select onchange={{action (mut model.demographicsAge) value="target.value"}} class="form-control" >
                  {{#each ageChoices as |ageChoice|}}
                    <option value={{ageChoice}} selected={{eq model.demographicsAge ageChoice}}>{{ageChoice}}</option>
                  {{/each}}
                </select>
                <label>What is your gender?</label>
                <select onchange={{action (mut model.demographicsGender) value="target.value"}} class="form-control" >
                  {{#each genderOptions as |genderOption|}}
                    <option value={{genderOption}} selected={{eq chosenGender genderOption}}>{{genderOption}}</option>
                  {{/each}}
                </select>
                <label>What is the highest level of education you've completed?</label>
                <select onchange={{action (mut model.demographicsEducationLevel) value="target.value"}} class="form-control" >
                  {{#each educationOptions as |educationOption|}}
                    <option value={{educationOption}} selected={{eq chosenEducation educationOption}}>{{educationOption}}</option>
                  {{/each}}
                </select>
                <label>What is the highest level of education your spouse has completed?</label>
                <select onchange={{action (mut model.demographicsSpouseEducationLevel) value="target.value"}} class="form-control" >
                  {{#each spouseEducationOptions as |spouseEducationOption|}}
                    <option value={{spouseEducationOption}} selected={{eq chosenSpouseEducation spouseEducationOption}}>{{spouseEducationOption}}</option>
                  {{/each}}
                </select>
                <label>What is your approximate family yearly income?</label>
                <select onchange={{action (mut model.demographicsAnnualIncome) value="target.value"}} class="form-control" >
                  {{#each annualIncomeOptions as |annualIncomeOption|}}
                    <option value={{annualIncomeOption}} selected={{eq chosenAnnualIncome annualIncomeOption}}>{{annualIncomeOption}}</option>
                  {{/each}}
                </select>
                <label>If you had been contacted on the phone by a local university about participating
                in studies like this, would you have been interested</label>
                <select onchange={{action (mut model.demographicsWillingToBeContactedForSimilarStudies) value="target.value"}} class="form-control" >
                  {{#each yesNoOptions as |yesNoOption|}}
                    <option value={{yesNoOption}} selected={{eq chosenParticipateOther yesNoOption}}>{{yesNoOption}}</option>
                  {{/each}}
                </select>
                <label>Would you have been able to schedule an appointment during the workweek to bring one of
                your children ~5 miles for this study?</label>
                <select onchange={{action (mut model.demographicsCanScheduleAnAppointment) value="target.value"}} class="form-control" >
                  {{#each yesNoOptions as |yesNoOption|}}
                    <option value={{yesNoOption}} selected={{eq chosenScheduleAppointment yesNoOption}}>{{yesNoOption}}</option>
                  {{/each}}
                </select>

                <label>Any additional comments?</label>
                    {{bs-input type="text" value=model.demographicsAdditionalComments}}
                <br />
                {{#bs-button type="primary" action="saveDemographicsPreferences"}}
                    Save
                {{/bs-button}}
            {{/bs-form-group}}
        {{/bs-form}}
    </div>
</div>